<statement>
<p>A triangle has sides with lengths <m>\displaystyle{a}={6.00}</m>, <m>\displaystyle{b}={6.95}</m>, and <m>\displaystyle{c}={8.36}</m>. Calculate all of the angles of this triangle.</p>
<p>A=<fillin characters="4" /> (across from side of length <m>\displaystyle{a}={6.00}</m>)</p>
<p>
  B=<fillin characters="4" /> (across from side of length <m>\displaystyle{b}={6.95}</m>)</p>
<p>
  C=<fillin characters="4" /> (across from side of length <m>\displaystyle{c}={8.36}</m>)</p>
<p>Round to two decimal places.</p>


</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>44.98</li><li>54.97</li><li>81.74</li></ul></p><p>Because we have all three sides, we can use the law of cosines for the first angle.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6}^{{2}}={6.95}^{{2}}+{8.36}^{{2}}-{2}{\left({6.95}\right)}{\left({8.36}\right)}{\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{36}={48.3025}+{69.8896}-{116.204}{\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{82.1921}=-{116.204}{\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{0.70730869849575}={\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{A}={44.983636612788}={44.98}</m>.</p>
<p>For a second angle, we can use the shorter law of sines.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle\frac{{\sin{{\left({44.983636612788}\right)}}}}{{6.00}}=\frac{{\sin{{\left({B}\right)}}}}{{6.95}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{0.97554131895168}={\sin{{\left({B}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{B}={\arcsin{{\left({0.97554131895168}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{B}={54.967982980479}\approx{54.97}</m></p>
<p>The third angle we can calculate using the angle sum property.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{44.983636612788}+{54.967982980479}+{C}={180}^{\circ}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{C}={81.739773519916}\approx{81.74}</m></p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

